<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-07-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-07-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="300" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d300">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Pro memoria.</hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Chinese Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-07-18"><hi rend="italic">July 18,
                                        1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>I have been requested by Grand Secretary Li Hung Chang to consult
                                your Government as to the possibility of obtaining from the treaty
                                powers either a guaranty of the territorial integrity of China or a
                                self-denying ordinance in any action circumstances may call on them
                                to take in the present disturbed state of the country.</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>